==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obvoluted
<hw>Ob`vo*lu"ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>obvolutus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>obvolvere</ets> to wrap round; <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>)
+ <ets>volvere</ets> to roll.]</ety> <def>Overlapping; contorted;
convolute; -- applied primarily, in botany, to two opposite leaves, each
of which has one edge overlapping the nearest edge of the other, and
secondarily to a circle of several leaves or petals which thus
overlap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oby</ent>⟦br⟧
